Global Public Health / History Joint Major    | Department of History | New York University                                    NEW YORK UNIVERSITY     ARTS AND SCIENCE     COLLEGE OF ARTS AND SCIENCE     GRADUATE SCHOOL OF ARTS AND SCIENCE             Department of History     Arts & Science                      Back to Home       Global Public Health / History Joint Major      About the Major:    The History Department has teamed up with NYU’s Global Institute of Public Health to develop a joint major in Global Public Health/History . This major offers the opportunity for students to deepen their understandings of issues related to public health, while also combining an interest in history, broadly defined, with preparation for a wide range of graduate programs and professional careers.          Majors in GPH/History have considerable freedom in their selection of History courses, not all of which need to have a strict public health dimension. Your advisors in the History Department will be happy to work with you in order to develop a program that complements and deepens your interests in public health – through such resources as internships, independent studies, and, for those who qualify, the honors thesis. For a course planning form that gives a sense of the shape of the GPH/History major, click here .     Declaring the Major:                      In order to declare the joint Global Public Health/History major, you must complete the  Declaration of Major Form for Global Public Health/History and submit it to the Undergraduate Administrative Assistant in the History Department. For questions related to the course of study and requirements, you may contact the Director of Undergraduate Studies (Professor Ortolano, ortolano@nyu.edu ) or the Undergraduate Program Assistant (Chelsea Rhodes, chelsea.rhodes@nyu.edu ).
